 25 2011 abstract since the crisis over america's debt rating and the formation of the super committee there has been a surge in debate about how to reduce defense spending despite talk of all options being on the table the lack of both breadth and depth in active proposals is remarkable efficiency initiatives and across the board cuts have been advanced as solutions however a more extensive list of tools must be considered to enrich the dialogue about defense cuts what follows is an a la carte menu of options to trim dod's investment accounts downloads pdf+ framing defense cuts by michael sulmeyer and guy ben ari modified november 2011 pdf 111025_diig_current_issues_26_ pdf 117.7 kb html+ go to site external http csis org publication diig cu parent research terrorism insurgency and homeland security topics investment united states search cisac publications everything publications of interest deep cuts in a peaceful world steps toward a minimum deterrent after start lawyers alliance for nuclear arms control 1989 deterrence and defense opportunities for a future european defense policy michael pene cisac 1997 simple model for calculating ballistic missile defense effectiveness a dean wilkening cisac 1998 pdf+ collaborative project on soviet defense conversion david m bernstein katherine smith cisac 1992 support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9625 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
